Wash and dry produce.

Peel and mince or grate @ginger{2%thumbs}(peeled and minced). Peel and mince or grate @garlic{2%cloves}(minced). Halve, peel, and thinly slice @onion{1}(halved, peeled, and sliced thinly). Quarter @lemon{1}. Place lemon wedges in a #small bowl{} and cover with #plastic wrap{}; refrigerate until ready to serve.

In a #medium microwave-safe bowl{}, whisk together @tomato paste{2%tbsp}, @cornstarch{2%tbsp}, and @water{1/4%cup}. Microwave until warmed through, about ~{30%seconds}.

Pat @chicken cutlets{20%oz} dry with #paper towels{}; cut into 1-inch pieces. Season with half the @cumin{1%tsp}, half the @turmeric{1%tsp}, half the @garam masala{1%tsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Place chicken in an even layer in a #5-to 6-quart slow cooker{}. Add @chicken stock concentrate{3}, tomato mixture, ginger, garlic, onion, remaining cumin, remaining turmeric, remaining garam masala, and @sugar{2%tsp}; stir to combine.

Cover and cook on high until chicken is cooked through and veggies are tender, about ~{90%minutes}.

Gently tear @spinach{5%oz} with your hands and add to slow cooker; stir to combine.

Cover slow cooker; cook on high until spinach is wilted, about ~{25-30%minutes}.

While spinach cooks, in a #large pot{}, combine @white rice{1.5%cup}, @water{2 1/4%cups}, and a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, about ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

Stir @crème fraîche{6%tbsp} into chicken saag until combined.

Divide rice between #shallow bowls{} and top with chicken saag. Serve with lemon wedges on the side.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.